    "last_activity_date" : 1763006725,
    "creation_date" : 1763006725,
    "answer_id" : 79818440,
    "question_id" : 43110640,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>ClassCastException: String cannot be cast to org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity.\n</code></pre>\n<p>This error says that you are casting a <strong>String</strong>  Object to <strong>ResponseEntity</strong> Object.You didn't shared the method <code>callService(url)</code> ,But according to your error it's clear that the <code>callService</code> method returned a <code>String</code> but it expects the  <code>ResponseEntity&lt;String&gt;</code> so to solve this either you must update the return type of the</p>\n<pre><code>callService(url)\n</code></pre>\n<p>or set this way</p>\n<pre><code>final String description = clientService.callService(url);\nResponseEntity&lt;String&gt; resEntity= ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.OK).body(description);\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
